# Active Directory Home Lab

##  Overview
Built a Windows Server Active Directory environment to simulate a real domain. 

Practiced user management, group policies, and domain joining.

---

##  Tools Used
- Windows Server
- Windows 10 Client VM
- VirtualBox

---

##  What I Built

- Installed and configured Windows Server
- Promoted server to a Domain Controller
- Created a domain 
- Created multiple user accounts and groups
- Joined a Windows client machine to the domain
- Configured Group Policy Objects 

---

##  Skills Practiced

- Active Directory user management
- Domain administration
- Group Policy configuration
- Windows networking basics
- Troubleshooting login and domain join issues

